    <div class="exercise">
        <span class="exercise-type timed-drill">Timed Drill</span>
        <h4>Three-Minute Evidence Hunt</h4>
        <p>Pick a controversial claim: "Social media harms teenagers." Set a three-minute timer. In that time, list as many types of evidence you could gather to support OR refute this claim. Don't evaluate—just generate. Categories might include: statistics, expert testimony, studies, examples, comparisons, mechanisms. After three minutes, review: Which evidence types came easily? Which did you overlook? Time pressure reveals your evidence-gathering instincts.</p>
    </div>

